        {
            "_id": "PrX599wjM2dd3n6F",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/ThreeActions.webp",
            "name": "Shadow Scream",
            "sort": 1000000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 3
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per hour</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The sacristans open their mouths in unison to unleash a chorus of ghastly wailing infused with the mind-shattering darkness of the Netherworld. This creates a @Template[type:emanation|distance:30] of darkness and pandemonium around it that's impenetrable even to creatures with darkvision (but not greater darkvision). They can Sustain Shadow Scream for up to 1 minute. Non-velstrac creatures in the area when the ability is used, as well as those that enter or start their turn in the area, must attempt a @Check[will|dc:33] save.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and is temporarily immune for 24 hours.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Deafened] for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Confused] and deafened for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[60[mental]|options:area-damage] damage and is confused and deafened for 1 round.</p>"
                },
                "frequency": {
                    "max": 1,
                    "per": "PT1H"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
